ry of medieval literary theory and criticism, Literature as Recreation in the Later Middle Ages makes use of medical, psychological, and sociological insights that lead to a fuller understanding of late medieval secular culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aAmusementszEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aBooks and readingzEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLiterature and societyzEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook Package Archivez978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501746758zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501746758zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501746758.jpg  a978-3-11-053617-1 COR eBook Package Archive  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA